or space - this is the usual way of building objects. 

Only XZH objects have truly 3D cursor movement. For these, the mouse 
controls movement along the ground (changing X and Z). And, provided 
you're not in auto height mode (toggled on/off by "H"), you press 
keyboard "-" and "+" (with or without shift), or move the mouse with 
its right button pressed, to change the height H above the ground. 


